 :tx/rationale "AUDIT F-CONC-001 (POSITIVE): Zero shared mutable state — excellent concurrency discipline. OBSERVATION: The kernel contains zero Arc<Mutex>, zero Rc<RefCell>, zero RwLock, and #![forbid(unsafe_code)]. The only shared state is a single AtomicUsize in harvest.rs for a spec candidate counter. The store is purely synchronous and single-threaded. All concurrency is external (multiple processes via filesystem with content-addressed files providing structural concurrency per SR-014). The aliasing discipline is: Store is owned not shared, all queries take &Store (immutable borrow), transactions consume self via typestate (Building -> Committed -> Applied), and the daemon process holds a single LiveStore instance. JUSTIFICATION: This validates ADR-STORE-006 (Embedded Deployment). By keeping the kernel single-threaded with ownership-based state management, the entire class of data races, deadlocks, and lock-ordering bugs is eliminated at the type level. The typestate pattern on Transaction provides compile-time enforcement of the transaction lifecycle. This is how Rust should be used for correctness-critical systems. SIGNIFICANCE: This is a positive finding — the architecture is sound. No action needed. DEPENDENCIES: None. This validates the existing design. FILES: Entire codebase. SEVERITY: N/A (positive finding)."
